Description: The Congressional Internet Caucus Advisory Committee is a group of NGOs .
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: The Congressional Internet Caucus Advisory Committee (ICAC) is part of a private sector organization comprised of public interest groups, trade associations, non-profits, and corporations. The ICAC takes no positions on legislation or regulation. Rather, it’s a neutral platform where thought leaders debate important technology issues that shape legislative and administration policy in an open forum. They vigilantly adhere to their mission to curate balanced and dynamic debates among Internet stakeholders. Their volunteer board members ensure that they dutifully execute that mission. IEF’s board of directors is comprised by public interest groups, corporations, and associations representative of the diversity of the Internet community. The Congressional Internet Caucus Advisory Committee works to educate policymakers on critical Internet policy issues. With funding and logistical support from the Internet Education Foundation, the Internet Caucus Advisory Committee hosts regular debates to discuss important Internet policy issues. The Internet Education Foundation, a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization dedicated to educating the public and policymakers about the potential of a decentralized global Internet to promote communications, commerce and democracy. Since its founding, the Internet Caucus Advisory Committee has built a membership of over 200 organizations from a broad cross-section of the public interest community and the Internet industry. Additional information, including an updated membership list, is available here.

There are no cheap or filler ingredients, and we NEVER grind, process, puree, or otherwise disguise our ingredients. In fact, our customers love the idea that they can visually identify the food in Real Meals for Dogs before they ever turn the package over. From the USDA graded meats & poultry to the USDA graded vegetables & fruits, every ingredient is suitable for a human table, and that's the new requirement of demanding customers. They want and expect the food they feed their four-legged family to be of the same quality and made with the same care as the food they eat.  freshfetch foods are unlike any other food for dogs that you'll find. And, no other food, currently produced, can even come close to the quality and care put into every freshfetch Real Meal for Dogs.

Description: TerraMaps is an interactive Terraria v1.3.1 world map viewer that loads quickly and lets the pan, zoom, find blocks, ores, items in chests.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Design and publish city maps of New York City, Washington DC and London [so far]  	 Our business started with just a few stores in 2010 with less than 1,000 maps sold per month and in three short years, we've grown to over 10,000 maps sold per month and expanded to include maps for London and Washington, DC.  Points of sale include museums, bookstores, bodegas, newsstands, gift shops, hotels, street vendors and some direct Internet sales which have coincidentally been a boon for us because we've been able to react to consumer demand by updating accordingly.   UV lamination allows us to provide a durable reusable high resolution map while being ecofriendly as well. Meanwhile, where we print small batches, i.e., 30,000 maps per 3 month cycle, other map companies seek to keep wholesale prices low by printing higher volumes.  As a result they are more likely to be outdated.  This was a deliberate choice on our part in order to provide vendors faster turnaround of inventory tailored to the area or type of point of sale they require.  Our vendors tell us that this approach allows our maps to sell better while some other maps that focus on streets rather than sites or have stale information collect dust on the store shelf.  Our design and style  led to a contract with Macy's to be their exclusive designer and printer of their own maps which highlight store locations and are used as a marketing tool for the giant retailer.  To summarize, our maps are portable, user-friendly, ecological, economical and handy.  They beat the alternatives available on the market in every category.

She has been working in the same position since she started working at the hospital where she used to work, so it seems likely that she was given a higher position there. Some of the things that bring her the most joy in the world are reading a good book, spending time with the people who are important to her, and doing other new and interesting things. When she has the chance, she puts herself in dangerous situations and has fun doing it. She really wants to see parts of the world that haven't been seen before, so she makes it a point to travel a lot to fill that need. Program elements include: (1) interdisciplinary, team-based learning combining engineering, clinical and business trainees; (2) intensive exposure to medical needs-finding and characterization; (3) “hands-on” process of invention, prototyping and early stage testing;  (4) practical instruction in regulatory, reimbursement, patenting and technology transfer; and (5) mentoring by highly experienced technology innovators, including Stanford faculty as well as a wide range of “real world” industry experts.

Description: Pick Your Bid is a shopping service app that helps customers compare prices.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: For whatever new item you want to buy, let retailers compete to give you the best deal at Pickyourbid.com! You live in a world where information comes to you - a message straight to your inbox, a push notification to your smart phone, news headlines on your twitter feed. So why isn’t online shopping that easy? Shoppers waste valuable hours comparing prices, delivery costs and warranties across hundreds of online stores and half baked price comparison sites every day. At the same time bricks and mortar retailers battle to compete in a digital market. That’s about to change. PickYourBid.com works the way online retail should. It’s not another group buying or daily deals site - PickYourBid is a better system that connects smart shoppers with savvy retailers to give customers the best possible deal. Shoppers: Get the best deal every time - no exceptions As a shopper your needs always come first. PickYourBid finds you unbeatable, personalized deals for the products you want - not the products retailers want to sell you. All you need to do is tell PickYourBid what you want and sit back while hundreds of local retailers and trusted online stores right across the country compete to offer you the best possible deal. You name the product and retailers offer you a price - not the other way around. There is no inventory list or shopping cart, no fees and no strings attached - you only buy the item if you’re happy with the deal presented to you. You have complete control. Retailers: Earn more customers by giving them a better deal The days of waiting for customers to walk through the front door or land on your home page are gone. PickYourBid brings customers to you in real time. There’s no guess work - PickYourBid lets you know exactly what each customer wants, giving you the chance to offer them your best deal. Whether that’s the lowest price, longest warranty, fastest shipping - it’s completely up to you. If the customer chooses your offer, you’re paid instantly. PickYourBid is a game changing shopping experience that will bring you more customers than you ever thought possible. The PickYourBid.com story PickYourBid is a new e-commerce platform founded by Josh Gorrell, a successful retailer tired of losing customers to online stores without a chance to compete. Josh created PickYourBid to level the playing field, give shoppers the best deal possible and put retailers back in the game. If you’d like to speak to Josh about PickYourBid or try it for yourself, email him directly at josh@pickyourbid.com or go to www.pickyourbid.com.
